==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prospectus
<hw>Pro*spec"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a prospect,
sight, view: cf. F. <ets>prospectus</ets>. See <er>Prospect</er>.]</ety>
<def>A summary, plan, or scheme of something proposed, affording a
prospect of its nature; especially, an exposition of the scheme of an
unpublished literary work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prosper</ent>⟦br⟧
